
## Running Ubuntu, "-d" making it daemon "-it" flag interactive terminal inside the spawned container ##
docker run -d -it ubuntu

## Lists containers ##
docker container ls

## Action - Look for the container ID ##
<grab the running container id for ubuntu>

## Run a command in a running container ##
docker exec -it <container-id> sh
<observe the different prompt>

## Exit the container ##
exit

## Attaching to the container ##
docker container attach <container-id>

## To turn interactive mode to daemon mode ##
ctrl+p followed by ctrl+q

## Lists containers ##
docker container ls

## kill the container ##
docker kill <container-id>

## Lists containers ##
docker container ls

